name: French elections
summary: In the second round of parliamentary elections in France, the left-wing Nouvelle Union Populaire Ecologique et Sociale (NUPES) has emerged as the largest party, securing the most seats in the National Assembly. The ruling centrist coalition led by President Emmanuel Macron's Ensemble came in second, while Marine Le Pen's far-right National Rally finished third. The high voter turnout reflected the high stakes of the election, with voters rejecting the far right and dealing a blow to Le Pen's ambitions. The results have led to a hung parliament, setting the stage for potential alliances and negotiations among the various parties.

Authorities in California are taking measures to prepare for the dangerous effects of the heatwave, including setting up cooling centers and urging residents to take precautions to stay safe. summary: Caitlin Clark, the star guard for the Indiana Fever, has made a significant impact in the WNBA. In a recent game against the New York Liberty, Clark recorded the franchise's first-ever triple-double, leading the Fever to a victory. Her performance has garnered attention, with many outlets covering the historic moment. Clark's impressive display and the Fever's rally after being down by 15 points have contributed to their recent success. Upcoming games, including a matchup against the New York Liberty, will be available to watch on Paramount+ and other platforms. Clark's journey and the Fever's progress will continue to be closely monitored, as they aim to continue their winning ways and make a strong showing in the league.

name: Ben Rice
summary: Ben Rice, a rookie outfielder from Cohasset, Massachusetts, made history as the first New York Yankees rookie to hit three home runs in a single game. In a 14-4 rout of the Boston Red Sox at Yankee Stadium, Rice's exceptional performance marked a significant milestone for the young player. His "magical" three-homer day has been hailed by ESPN, while The Patriot Ledger praised the Cohasset native's impressive feat against his hometown team. The New York Post described the debut as a "full-circle moment" in the Yankees-Red Sox rivalry. Bleacher Report highlighted Rice's historic achievement with a video showcasing his home runs, earning cheers from Yankees fans who hailed him as an unsung hero. CBS Sports and FOX Sports also acknowledged Rice's history-making performance, emphasizing his three-run homer that extended the Yankees' lead over the Red Sox.
